# Platform preprocessor and #endif comments

When editing code with `#ifdef _WIN32` / `#ifdef __APPLE__` / `#ifdef __linux__`:

## Do not change platform code for “cross-platform”

Do **not** modify code inside platform blocks to make it cross-platform (e.g. do not change `\\` to `/` inside `#ifdef _WIN32`). To make behavior cross-platform, refactor to a platform-agnostic abstraction with separate implementations per platform.

## Always comment #endif

Add a **matching comment** after **every** `#endif` (for any `#if`, `#ifdef`, or `#ifndef`). Two spaces before `//`. The comment should repeat the condition (e.g. `#endif  // _WIN32`, `#endif  // NOMINMAX`).

```cpp
// ❌ WRONG
#endif

// ✅ CORRECT
#endif  // _WIN32
#endif  // LOGGING_ENABLED
#endif  // NOMINMAX
```

For **#define** usage (when to use macros vs constexpr, how to comment macros), see `.cursor/rules/preprocessor-macros-define.mdc`.

Full details: AGENTS.md (Core C++17 conventions, includes and platform blocks).
